HEADWORD: Rudderstock
<hw>Rud"der*stock`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>The main part or blade of the rudder, which is connected by hinges,
or the like, with the sternpost of a vessel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

